  "body": "I'm reading the lodestar network code and I have some questions that may be easier to answer with code blocks here in Github.\r\n\r\n**eth2RequestEncode serialize error**\r\n\r\n`eth2RequestEncode()` is used exclusively here\r\nhttps://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/b787fe3cbcb670f1e0d52140540cc33a045313dc/packages/lodestar/src/network/reqresp/reqUtils.ts#L76\r\nWhere the source will have always 1 request max. Then if that single request fails to be serialized the `eth2RequestEncode` will call continue and on the source and what would happen then? Will that request be ignored? Would there be an error downstream? Is that request considered ok, failed or just disappears?\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/b787fe3cbcb670f1e0d52140540cc33a045313dc/packages/lodestar/src/network/encoders/request.ts#L24-L30",
